import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    plt.hist(data['values'], bins='auto')
    plt.xlabel('Values')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.title('What is the distribution of values in the volcano dataset?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    plt.boxplot(data['values'])
    plt.xticks([1], ['values'])
    plt.title("What is the average value of the volcano dataset?")
    plt.axhline(data['values'].mean(), color='r', linestyle='--', label=f"Mean: {data['values'].mean():.2f}")
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()
